cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of computer science that studies the aggregation of individual preferences to make collective decisions. The use of metric spaces and the consideration of both proposing and voting make it likely that the paper belongs to cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study of solution concepts and the comparison to known voting rules suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of mathematical optimization techniques and the consideration of various applications make it possible that the paper belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
